v2026.4.25.2 - Windows probe support

Adds Windows enrollment alongside the existing Linux flow so operators
can install the Sonar Probe on Windows hosts straight from the Agents
page.

Backend:
* internal/probe: split fingerprint by GOOS — Windows reads
  HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Cryptography!MachineGuid via reg.exe, Linux
  keeps /etc/machine-id et al. osVersion() now switches on GOOS and
  shells `cmd /c ver` on Windows.
* cmd/sonar-probe: new run_windows.go wraps probe.Run with a proper
  SCM service handler (golang.org/x/sys/windows/svc) so the binary
  works as the SonarProbe Windows service or in the foreground.
  Default config path is %ProgramData%\Sonar\agent.json on Windows.
* docker/api.Dockerfile: probebuild stage now also cross-compiles
  windows/amd64 -> sonar-probe.exe and embeds it under
  internal/probebins/bin/windows/amd64.
* internal/api/handlers_probe.go: allowedProbePlatforms includes
  windows/amd64; download serves sonar-probe.exe with the right
  filename. New /api/v1/probe/install.ps1 endpoint serves a
  PowerShell installer that downloads the exe, enrolls, registers
  the SonarProbe service via sc.exe, and starts it.
* internal/api/handlers_agents.go: createEnrollmentToken response now
  carries an installCmds {linux, windows} bundle. The legacy
  installCmd field stays on the linux command for back-compat.
* OpenAPI spec updated for the new arch enum, install.ps1 path, and
  installCmds schema.

Frontend:
* Agents page: after issuing a token, show OS tabs (Linux / Windows)
  with the matching one-liner; copy button copies the active tab.
* Types: NewEnrollmentToken now exposes installCmds.

Versioning: bump VERSION, web/package.json, package-lock.json,
Layout APP_VERSION, and openapi.yaml info.version to 2026.4.25.2.
go.mod promotes golang.org/x/sys to a direct require.
